<subSubSection id="638583A73D4CB12FE82711DE18E30671" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="description">
<paragraph id="E6407D45637FD0776970FD6E8560D929" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6D69BFD848E14FA8A087564E790F381F" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Twining perennial; stems sericeous, somewhat woody, and wiry. Leaves shortly petiolate, 2.3-6.5 
<normalizedToken id="B1FDC3E414BE3C7F12ECB4F946D60532" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.8-3.2 cm, oblong-ovate, base cuneate to weakly cordate, apex acute and shortly mucronate, adaxially dark green, densely pubescent, abaxially densely grey-velutinous, shiny; petioles 3-8 mm, sericeous. Inflorescence of pedunculate axillary cymes with up to 12 flowers; peduncles 1.4-3 cm, grey-tomentose; bracteoles linear, 3-6 
<normalizedToken id="91CB9F0B7BB45BC959A57E0FD94F0139" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1 mm, densely tomentose; secondary peduncles 3-12 mm, tomentose; pedicels 4-7 mm, thickened upwards and becoming less tomentose; sepals subequal, outer 5-6 
<normalizedToken id="0E4E0CCB993828E02E9D92373C0D404B" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
3-4 mm, pubescent towards base, glabrescent, inner 6-8 
<normalizedToken id="7852C287BCD69421FC01640599DF6E99" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
4 mm, ovate, obtuse to rounded, reddish-brown, coriaceous, glabrous, margin narrow, palid; corolla 3-3.5 cm long, pink, glabrous, narrowly funnel-shaped; limb c. 1.5 cm diam.; stamens included. Capsules 10-11 
<normalizedToken id="765D4A3D631B0F24F9D4FB434E712638" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
5-6 mm, ovoid, glabrous, muticous; seeds 5 
<normalizedToken id="EAC406235D7C4FBEB09AAC7F3F51DAB0" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
3 mm, blackish, with long marginal hairs up to 10 mm long.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
